        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive National Mercury Monitoring Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill requires the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to establish&amp;nbsp;a national mercury monitoring program. Under the program, the EPA must track and report on long-term changes of mercury concentrations in air, water, soil, and fish and wildlife.&amp;nbsp;In addition, the EPA must establish an online database for mercury data.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
